Q2 : implement redis cache in spring boot application? 
Redis is a kind of database
Implementing Redis cache in a Spring Boot application is a common way to improve performance and reduce database load.
Below is a complete step-by-step guide with explanations and code examples.

рЯІ∞ 1. Add Dependencies

If youвАЩre using Maven, add the following dependencies to your pom.xml:

