    @Cacheable(value = "users", key = "#id") // 'value' defines the cache name, 'key' defines how the cache entry is identified 
    public String getUserById(String id) {
        System.out.println("Fetching user from database for ID: " + id);
        return "User_" + id;
    }
}


When you call getUserById("101"):

The first call hits the database (or your logic).

The result is cached in Redis under key users::101.

Subsequent calls return instantly from cache.

рЯІє 6. Cache Eviction Example

If data changes and you want to clear or update the cache:

import org.springframework.cache.annotation.CacheEvict;
import org.springframework.cache.annotation.CachePut;

@Service
